snippet.textDisplay:
I am 29 years old and an ordinary Korean man. In fact, I and many other Koreans laughed at the BTS at first.
Just because the group's name was weird.
I happen to see them win the prize on the news in 2018 or so. I searched YouTube for them. Even when the song "DNA" came out, I ignored it.
Ever since they became famous, they began to look new.
I searched for more and more videos, and broke my prejudice that their choreography or songs would be similar to traditional mass production model idol groups(Typical K-pop Idol Style)
I watched with my heart, "Yes, how well they did and drove people this crazy," and ended up mesmerizing..
It occurred to me that they were living harder than anyone else(I've seen Jungkook fall down from exhaustion while working hard on stage)And I felt sorry for the moments when I hated them..
Since then, they have accomplished many things beyond my expectations.
And that passion became a hope in my life. Now I'm rooting for ARMY and BTS.
snippet.textOriginal:
I am 29 years old and an ordinary Korean man. In fact, I and many other Koreans laughed at the BTS at first. 
Just because the group's name was weird.
I happen to see them win the prize on the news in 2018 or so. I searched YouTube for them. Even when the song "DNA" came out, I ignored it.
Ever since they became famous, they began to look new.
I searched for more and more videos, and broke my prejudice that their choreography or songs would be similar to traditional mass production model idol groups(Typical K-pop Idol Style)
I watched with my heart, "Yes, how well they did and drove people this crazy," and ended up mesmerizing..
It occurred to me that they were living harder than anyone else(I've seen Jungkook fall down from exhaustion while working hard on stage)And I felt sorry for the moments when I hated them..
Since then, they have accomplished many things beyond my expectations.
And that passion became a hope in my life. Now I'm rooting for ARMY and BTS.

snippet.textDisplay: Listen. Coordinating those transitions flawlessly is absolutely mind-blowing. As a dancer, I know what it is like and things never go right. A prop goes missing, a stage is brought late, it throws EVERYONE off. But this was flawlessly executed and amazing to watch. The choreo itself is phenomenal and the boys dance it very well. I literally had to reply portions to understand what the hell just happened. and jimin, sweetie, you hit every. single. freaking. beat so effortlessly.
